 for anyone else interested in how the legal system responds to injustice. In Restitution, Ward Farnsworth presents a guide to this body of law that is compact, lively, and insightful—the first treatment of its kind that the American law of restitution has received. The book explains restitution doctrines, remedies, and defenses with unprecedented clarity and illustrates them with vivid examples. Farnsworth demonstrates that the law of restitution is guided by a manageable and coherent set of principles that have remarkable versatility and power. Restitution makes a complex and important area of law accessible, understandable, and interesting to any reader.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aRestitution -- United States. 0aRestitutionzUnited States. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh  alaw, legal issues, litigation, ponzi scheme, money, fraud, theft, stealing, criminal, crime, stocks, shareholder, dividends, academic, scholarly, finance, financial, economics, economy, rights, defendant, lawyer, courtroom, judge, jury, gains, justice, injustice, american, america, united states, contracts, remedies, solutions, school, college, university, higher ed, textbook, analysis, defense.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311069043940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226144337423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226144337/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles